==English==

===Etymology===
From the Russian [[кулак]] ''(kulák)'', or ''[[fist]].'' Recog. in English in 1877.

===Noun===
'''kulak'''
# A prosperous landed peasant in tsarist Russia.
# A farmer whom Communists in Soviet Russia deemed to be wealthy.
